-- Allot Surges Toward Record, Narrows Gap With U.S. Traded Shares
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-05-30T08:02:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-30/allot-surges-toward-record-narrows-gap-with-u-s-traded-shares.html
Allot Communications Ltd. (ALLT)  headed for
the highest close on record, narrowing the gap with the U.S.-
traded stock of the Israeli maker of high-speed networking
equipment.  The  shares  of the Hod Hasharon, Israel-based company
advanced 7.9 percent, the most since May 1 in intraday trading,
to 101.3 shekels, or the equivalent of $26.14, at 10:30 a.m. in
 Tel Aviv . The stock added 11 percent to $26.40 in New York
yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
